page.title: 05Cetti's Warbler in Bas/stoke
page.content: When I was doing the YOC sponsored {birdwatch}down at Blackdam{Nature {Centre}I saw a rare bird called a {Cetti's Warbler. This bird was nearly{extinct}but with the help of the{Royal Society for the {Protection of Birds}it is coming back. That afternoon I telephoned the Royal Society for the Protection of Birds HQ at The Lodge. They sent a member down to Blackdam to see if the bird I saw had a mate and to see if it was breeding, as I saw the{Cetti's {Warbler}in May which is the{breeding {season}for most birds. Unfortunately it was not breeding but the RSPB will do a survey next year in the breeding season. Blackdam is a Nature Reserve. It is maintained by{volunteers}and offers a haven for wild birds and small animals.It is next to the M3 Motorway.
